Package org.swerverobotics.library.examples

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    LinearAutonomousPolygon
    This autonomous OpMode drives the robot forward for a while, turns left, then drives forward again and turns left, etc, until a polygon has been completed.
    LinearColorDemo
    This LinearOpMode illustrates a very simple use of the Swerve color sensor implementation.
    LinearMotorLoopPerf
    An op mode that investigates how fast in a Linear OpMode we can execute a main loop that both reads and writes to the a motor.
    LinearTelemetryOp
    An example that illustrates use of the telemetry dashboard and log in a linear opmode
    SynchAnalogOutputDemo
    SynchAnalogOutputDemo is a short demo of an AnalogOutput port.
    SynchAutoDriveEncoders
    This simple OpMode illustrates how to drive autonomously a certain distance using encoders.
    SynchAutoPolygon
    This synchronous OpMode makes the the robot move in the shape of (approximately) a simple polygon using time-based motion limits.
    SynchAutoPolygonEncoders
    This is similar to LinearAutonomousPolygon, but uses a 'run to position' approach rather than a timed delay approach for determining when events should end.
    SynchAutoServoDemo
    This simple OpMode illustrates the basic use of a servo from a synchronous OpMode.
    SynchColorDemo
    This SynchronousOpMode illustrates a very simple use of the Swerve color sensor implementation, which is used automatically.
    SynchIMUDemo
    SynchIMUDemo gives a short demo on how to use the BNO055 Inertial Motion Unit (IMU) from AdaFruit.
    SynchLEDDemo
    SynchLEDDemo is a short demo on using the digital output pins to light an LED.
    SynchMotorLoopPerf
    An op mode that investigates how many loop() cycles it takes to do full mode switching on a motor controller.
    SynchServoDemo
    This is an example showing the use of servos.
    SynchSkeletalOp
    This is a very simple placeholder.
    SynchTelemetryOp
    An example that illustrates use of the telemetry dashboard and log in a synchronous OpMode
    SynchTeleOp
    An example of a synchronous opmode that implements a simple drive-a-bot.
    SynchTeleOpModes
    An example of a synchronous opmode that's a little more complex than SynchTeleOp, in that it supports multiple different drive modes that are switched between using the A, B, and Y gamepad buttons.
